    • isValidAux

      protected boolean isValidAux(TreeNode<T> node, TreeNode<T> minNode, TreeNode<T> maxNode)
      Auxiliary method for valid. Determines if a subtree based on node is a valid subtree. An Popularity Tree must meet the BST validation conditions, and additionally the counts of any node data must be greater than or equal to the counts of its children.
      Overrides:
      isValidAux in class BST<T extends Comparable<T>>
      Parameters:
      node - The root of the subtree to test for validity.
      minNode - The node of the minimum data in the current subtree.
      maxNode - The node of the maximum data in the current subtree.
      Returns:
      true if the subtree base on node is valid, false otherwise.
